#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga "
msgstr "2. At Nālandā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 20. Janapadakalyāṇīsutta → janapada (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Janapadakalyāṇīsutta "
msgstr "20. The Finest Lady in the Land "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.170, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.20:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn47.20:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sumbhesu viharati sedakaṃ nāma sumbhānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sumbhas, near the town of the Sumbhas called Sedaka. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

# NOTE: Woodward and Thanissaro attribute the words to the crowd. I’m not sure which is correct, but I follow BB. See BB for notes on this and paramapasavani
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.20:2.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ‘janapadakalyāṇī, janapadakalyāṇī’ti kho, bhikkhave, mahājanakāyo sannipateyya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose that on hearing, ‘The finest lady in the land! The finest lady in the land!’ a large crowd would gather. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.2"
msgid "‘Sā kho panassa janapadakalyāṇī paramapāsāvinī nacce, paramapāsāvinī gīte. "
msgstr "And the finest lady in the land would dance and sing in a most thrilling way. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.3"
msgid "Janapadakalyāṇī naccati gāyatī’ti kho, bhikkhave, bhiyyoso mattāya mahājanakāyo sannipateyya. "
msgstr "On hearing, ‘The finest lady in the land is dancing and singing! The finest lady in the land is dancing and singing!’ an even larger crowd would gather. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:2.4"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo. "
msgstr "Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "They’d say to him, "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, ambho purisa, samatittiko telapatto antarena ca mahāsamajjaṃ antarena ca janapadakalyāṇiyā pariharitabbo. "
msgstr "‘Mister, this is a bowl full to the brim with oil. You must carry it in between this large crowd and the finest lady in the land. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.7"
msgid "Puriso ca te ukkhittāsiko piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhissati. "
msgstr "And a man with a drawn sword will follow behind you. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.8"
msgid "Yattheva naṃ thokampi chaḍḍessati tattheva te siro pātessatī’ti. "
msgstr "Wherever you spill even a drop, he’ll chop off your head right there.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.10"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ telapattaṃ amanasikaritvā bahiddhā pamādaṃ āhareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would that person lose focus on that bowl, and negligently get distracted outside?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:2.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.1"
msgid "“Upamā kho myāyaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya. "
msgstr "“I’ve made up this simile to make a point. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho—"
msgstr "And this is what it means. "

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.3"
msgid "samatittiko telapattoti kho, bhikkhave, kāyagatāya etaṃ satiyā adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘A bowl of oil filled to the brim’ is a term for mindfulness of the body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.5"
msgid "‘kāyagatā sati no bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will develop mindfulness of the body. We’ll cultivate it, make it our vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement it.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.6"
msgid "Evañhi kho, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.8"
msgid "Nālandavaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.171, sc4
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.1"
msgid "Mahāpuriso nālandaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.2"
msgid "Cundo celañca bāhiyo; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.3"
msgid "Uttiyo ariyo brahmā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.4"
msgid "Sedakaṃ janapadena cāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
